    "body": "## Purpose\n* continue refactoring / standardizing MoEs to use the mks\n* convert AITER to an mk, call it from fp8.py\n* fix bug where fp8 triton was broken on ROCm\n\n## Test Plan\n- on AMD\n\n```bash\nMODEL := \"Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B-Instruct-FP8\"\nPORT := \"8000\"\n\nlaunch:\n\tVLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER=1 VLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER_MOE=1 vllm serve {{MODEL}} --enforce-eager --port {{PORT}}\n\neval LIMIT:\n\tlm_eval \\\n\t\t--model local-completions \\\n\t\t--tasks gsm8k \\\n\t\t--model_args \"model={{MODEL}},base_url=http://localhost:{{PORT}}/v1/completions,num_concurrent=1000,tokenized_requests=False\" \\\n\t\t--limit {{LIMIT}}\n```\n\n- on NVIDIA\n```bash\nMODEL := \"Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B-Instruct-FP8\"\n\nlaunch_fi:\n\tVLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0 VLLM_USE_FLASHINFER_MOE_FP8=1  vllm serve {{MODEL}}\n\nlaunch_dg:\n\tVLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=1 VLLM_MOE_USE_DEEP_GEMM=1 vllm serve {{MODEL}}\n\nlaunch_triton:\n\tVLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0 VLLM_MOE_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0 vllm serve {{MODEL}}\n\nlaunch_marlin:\n\tVLLM_TEST_FORCE_FP8_MARLIN=1 VLLM_USE_DEEP_GEMM=0 vllm serve {{MODEL}}\n\neval LIMIT:\n\tlm_eval \\\n\t\t--model local-completions \\\n\t\t--tasks gsm8k \\\n\t\t--model_args \"model={{MODEL}},base_url=http://localhost:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=1000,tokenized_requests=False\" \\\n\t\t--limit {{LIMIT}}\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\n```bash\nlocal-completions (model=Qwen/Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B-Instruct-FP8,base_url=http://localhost:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=1000,tokenized_requests=False), gen_kwargs: (None), limit: 100.0, num_fewshot: None, batch_size: 1\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value|   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.90|±  |0.0302|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.93|±  |0.0256|\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
